 <pb n="1" id="Tw8212121">  
<div1 type="letter"> 
<opener> 
<seg> 
<figure entity="T821212a"> 
<figDesc>Papers of Mark Twain,  AL 1882 Dec 12; 
Mark Twain, Hartford, CT., to Horace Russell; 
image of page one of the manuscript. 
</figDesc> 
</figure> 
</seg> 
<dateline> 
<name type="place">Hartford,</name> 
<date n="1882-12-12"><abbr expan="December">Dec.</abbr> 12/82.</date> 
</dateline> 
<salute>My Dear Judge Russell-</salute></opener> 
 
<p>Woodford <del>[illeg.]</del> wrote me, &amp; I <lb> 
answered; result, this arrangement: </p> 
 
<p><abbr expan="fifth">5<hi rend="sup">th</hi></abbr> Regular toast: <lb> 
Woman &mdash; God bless her! <lb> 
Response by Mark Twain.</p> 
 
<p>You see, I never use any <add place="supralinear">name</add> but my <lb> 
nom de guerre on public occasions.) </p> 
 
<p>Woodford says that if President <lb> 
<del>a</del><add place="overwritten">A</add>rthur is not on hand, I'll be <abbr expan="Number">No.</abbr> <lb> 
5 &mdash; otherwise I am to be <abbr expan="Number">No.</abbr> 6.  It <lb> 
gives me the belly-ache to wait long with <lb> 
a speech in my bowels. </p> 
 
<p>I threw aside all my other <orig reg="subjects">sub- <lb> 
jects</orig> &mdash; they were too solemn.  As <lb> 
this is to be my last speech, with the <lb> 
exception of one next August which <lb> 
 
   <pb n="2" id="Tw8212122">  
 
<figure entity="T821212b"> 
<figDesc>Papers of Mark Twain,  AL 1882 Dec 12; 
